meta {
  name: Run Ollama
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

post {
  url: {{aiUwLambdaUrl}}/workflows/collateral-review-v2-ollama/run
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "pdf_url": "{{pdf_url}}"
  }
}

docs {
  Run the v2 collateral-review pipeline against the Ollama Cloud backend.

  Routing:
    Bruno → Function URL → ai-uw-dispatcher → ai-uw-collateral-review-v2-ollama

  The dispatcher matches `collateral-review-v2-ollama` in WORKFLOW_ROUTING and
  invokes the Lambda whose `AI_BACKEND` env var is set to `ollama`. That Lambda
  uses the Node.js server's model stack on Ollama Cloud:
    OLLAMA_TEXT_MODEL            = gemma4:31b-cloud         (extract + analyze)
    OLLAMA_VISION_MODEL          = qwen3-vl:235b-cloud      (photo analysis)
    OLLAMA_DRAFTER_MODEL         = gpt-oss:120b-cloud       (review-chain drafter)
    OLLAMA_DRAFTER_FALLBACK_MODEL = gemma4:31b-cloud

  Required SSM secret: `/ai-uw/ollama-api-key` (set via the AWS console or
  `aws ssm put-parameter --name /ai-uw/ollama-api-key --value <key> --type SecureString --overwrite`).
  Other Ollama config (`OLLAMA_BASE_URL`, `OLLAMA_*_MODEL`) is wired in
  `template.yaml` with sensible defaults.

  Cold-start expectation: gemma4:31b cold starts on Ollama Cloud can take
  several minutes. The Lambda is configured with `Timeout: 900` and is
  invoked via the dispatcher Function URL (15-min headroom), so long cold
  runs that would 503 through API Gateway succeed here. Hot calls return in
  ~30-90s depending on PDF size.

  Use this side-by-side with `Run Gemini` and `Run OpenAI` to compare outputs
  on the same PDF. The repo also includes `make compare PDF_URL=...` and
  `tests/comparison/` for an automated parity harness.

  Response shape (success):
    {
      "success": true,
      "appraisal_id": "...",
      "scores": { ... },
      "risk_flags": [ ... ],
      "extracted": { ... }
    }
}
